## How to Run This Project

### 1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/favorita-store-sales-forecasting.git
```

### 2. Install required Python packages

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 3. Open the notebook

Open the Jupyter Notebook file:

```text
notebooks/favorita_sales_forecasting.ipynb
```

Run the notebook step by step to reproduce the data cleaning, feature engineering, modeling, and prediction process.

### 4. Open the Power BI dashboard

Open the `.pbix` file located in the `powerbi/` folder using Power BI Desktop.

## Power BI Report

The Power BI report was created to present the forecasting results in a clear business format. It helps users understand sales trends, compare store performance, analyze product families, and review model-based forecasting results.

The Power BI dashboard is useful because it turns the machine learning results into visual insights that can support business decisions.

